obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `The City of Bombay Municipal (Supplementary) Act, 1888`
  line `A CT N O. XII OF 1888.`
  line `P ASSED BY THE G OVERNOR G ENERAL OF I NDIA IN C OUNCIL.`
  line `( Received the assent of the Governor General on the 12th October,1888. )`
  line `An Act to supplement certain provisions of the City of Bombay Municipal Act, 1888, and of the`
  line `Calcutta Municipal Consolidation Act,1889.`
  line `W HEREAS it is expedient to supplement by legislation in the Council of the Governor General for`
  line `making Laws and Regulations certain provisions of the City of Bombay Municipal Act, 1888, and of`
  line `the Calcutta Municipal Consolidation Act, 1889; It is hereby enacted as follows: —`
  line `1. Confirmation of the City of Bombay Municipal Act, 1888, and the Calcutta Municipal`
  line `Consolidation Act,1889, so far as regards Benches, Magistrates and Courts of Small Causes`
  line `.—The City of Bombay Municipal Act,1888, and the Calcutta Municipal Consolidation Act,1889,`
  line `shall, so far as regards—`
  line `( a ) the jurisdiction thereby conferred upon Appellate Benches of Municipal Authorities and upon`
  line `Presidency and other Magistrates and Courts of Small Causes or any Judge of such a Court, and`
  line `( b ) the decisions, orders and other proceedings of those Benches, Magistrates and Courts or of`
  line `any such Judge,`
  line `be as valid as if they had been passed by the Governor General of India in Council at a meeting`
  line `for the purpose of making Laws and Regulations.`
  line `2. Reference of questions by the Chief Judge of the Bombay Small Cause Court to the Bombay`
  line `High Court.— ( 1 ) If before or on the hearing of an appeal under section 217 of the City of Bombay`
  line `Municipal Act,1888, any question of law or usage having the force of law, or the construction of a`
  line `document, which construction may affect the merits, arises, on which the Chief Judge of the Court of`
  line `Small Causes of Bombay entertains reasonable doubt, the Chief Judge may, either of his own motion or`
  line `on the application of either or any of the parties, draw up a statement of the facts of the case and the`
  line `point on which doubt is entertained, and refer the statement, with his own opinion on the point, for the`
  line `decision of the High Court of Judicature at Bombay.`
  line `( 2 ) When a reference is made to the High Court under sub-section ( 1 ), the provisions of sections`
  line `618 to 621, both inclusive, of the Code of Civil Procedure (XIV of 1882.) shall, so far as they can be`
  line `made applicable, apply to the Chief Judge of the Court of Small Causes and to the High Court,`
  line respectively.
  line `3. Appeal to the Bombay High Court from certain orders of the Chief Judge of the Bombay`
  line `Small Cause Court.— ( 1 ) An appeal shall lie to the High Court of Judicature at Bombay from a`
  line `decision passed by the Chief Judge of the Court of Small Causes of Bombay under section 503 or`
  line `section 504 of the City of Bombay Municipal Act, 1888, when the amount of the claim in respect of`
  line `which the decision is passed exceeds two thousand rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure (XIV of 1882.) with respect to appeals from`
  line `original decrees shall, so far as they can be mad applicable, apply to appeals under sub-section ( 1 ), and`
  line `orders passed therein by the High Court may, on application to the Chief Judge of the Court of Small`
  line `Causes, be executed by him as if they were decrees made by himself.`
