obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `( 3 ) A decision passed by the Chief Judge of the Court of Small Causes of Bombay under section`
  line `503 or section 504 of the City of Bombay Municipal Act, 1888, shall, if an appeal does not lie`
  line `therefrom under sub-section ( 1 ), be final.`
  line `4. Appeal to the Bombay High Court from orders of Presidency Magistrates in Bombay.— ( 1 )`
  line `An appeal shall lie to the High Court of Judicature at Bombay from an order passed by a Presidency`
  line `Magistrate under section 515 of the City of Bombay Municipal Act, 1888.`
  line `( 2 ) The High Court may from time to time make rules for regulating the admission of appeals under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) and the procedure to be followed in the adjudication thereof.`
  line `( 3 ) When an appeal has been preferred to the High Court under this section, the Municipal`
  line `Commissioner for the City of Bombay shall defer action upon the order of the Presidency Magistrate`
  line `until the appeal has been disposed of.`
  line `( 4 ) But, when the appeal has been disposed of, he shall forthwith give effect to the order passed`
  line `therein by the High Court, or, if the order of the Presidency Magistrate has not been disturbed by the`
  line `High Court, then to his order.`
  line `( 5 ) When disposing of an appeal under this section the High Court may direct by whom the costs of`
  line `the appeal are to be paid, and whether in whole or in what part or proportion.`
  line `(6) Costs so directed to be paid may, on application to a Presidency Magistrate, be recovered by`
  line `him, in accordance with the direction of the High Court, as if they were a fine imposed by himself.`
  line `5. Period of limitation for appeals to the Bombay High Court under the two last foregoing`
  line `sections.— An appeal to the High Court of Judicature at Bombay under either of the two last foregoing`
  line `sections shall, for the purposes of No. 156 of the second schedule to the Indian Limitation Act,`
  line `1877(XV of 1877.), be deemed to be an appeal under the Code of Civil Procedure(XIV of 1882.) in a`
  line `case not provided for by No. 151 and No. 153 of that schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
